title: $:/plugins/nikorion/math/readme
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

!! Overview

A lightweight TiddlyWiki widget integrating Math.js for inline expression evaluation.

Key capabilities:

* locale-aware output formatting (EN/FR/any BCP-47)
* input in standard EN notation (decimal point, scientific notation)
* configurable numeric precision: native float (default) or BigNumber (64 / 128 / 256 significant digits)
* unit-aware output with automatic simplification and explicit conversion
* LRU result cache for performance
* static expression validation with friendly error messages and "did you mean?" suggestions
* KaTeX rendering for results and formulas (automatic if KaTeX plugin is installed)

---

!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Values |!Default |!Description |
| `show` |`result` · `formula` · `full` |`result` |What to display — result only, formula only, or both |
| `mode` |`inline` · `block` |`inline` |KaTeX display mode — inline or centred block |
| `locale` |`en` · `en-US` · `fr` · `fr-FR` · BCP-47 |`en` |Output number format (separators, decimal symbol) |
| `notation` |`auto` · `fixed` · `scientific` · `engineering` · `bin` · `oct` · `hex` |`auto` |Numeric output notation |
| `precision` |positive integer |6 |Display digits — decimal places for `auto`/`fixed`, significant digits for `scientific`/`engineering`; ignored for `bin`/`oct`/`hex` |
| `calcPrec` |`float` · `64` · `128` · `256` |`float` |Arithmetic precision mode — see warning below |
| `scope` |tiddler title or `{a:1, b:2}` |— |Variable scope injected into the expression |
| `silence` |`yes` · `no` |`no` |Suppress expression error display |

!!! `show` attribute

;`show="result"` (default)
:Evaluates the expression and renders the numeric result via KaTeX (or plain text if KaTeX unavailable).

;`show="formula"`
:Converts the expression to LaTeX via `math.parse().toTex()` and renders it via KaTeX. The expression is ''not'' evaluated. `notation`, `precision`, `calcPrec`, and `scope` are ignored.

;`show="full"`
:Renders the formula and its evaluated result together: `formula = result` in a single KaTeX block.

!!! `mode` attribute

;`mode="inline"` (default)
:KaTeX renders inline with surrounding text.

;`mode="block"`
:KaTeX renders as a centred display-mode formula (larger, on its own line).

!!! `notation` attribute

|!Value |!Behaviour |!Default `precision` |
| `auto` |decimal for most values; scientific for |x| < 1e-6 or |x| > 1e12 |6 |
| `fixed` |always decimal |6 |
| `scientific` |always scientific: `1.414 \times 10^{3}` |6 |
| `engineering` |exponent always a multiple of 3 |6 |
| `bin` |binary integer, prefixed `0b` — e.g. `0b101010` |ignored |
| `oct` |octal integer, prefixed `0o` — e.g. `0o52` |ignored |
| `hex` |hexadecimal integer, prefixed `0x` — e.g. `0xff` |ignored |

''bin/oct/hex rules:''

* `locale` and `precision` are ignored — output is always plain ASCII.
* BigNumber results are converted via `toNumber()` before formatting.
* Negative values are accepted: `-42` → `-0b101010`.
* Non-integer values are truncated silently by math.js: `3.7` → `0b11`.
* Unit results produce an error — extract the numeric value first with `number(expr, unit)`.
* KaTeX output uses `\texttt{}` for monospace rendering.

All decimal/scientific modes default to 6 — readable without being lossy for most scientific/technical uses. Math.js generic default is 14 (matches IEEE 754 double precision but too verbose for a display widget). The `precision` attribute overrides this per widget.

!!! When is `silence="yes"` useful?

`silence="yes"` suppresses errors that arise from the ''expression itself'' — not from widget configuration. It is useful when:

* The expression depends on a TiddlyWiki variable (`<<myVar>>`) not yet defined.
* A table where some cells have no value yet, causing expressions to fail temporarily.
* A live-preview context where the expression is typed incrementally.

The 200 ms debounce already covers momentary invalidity while typing. `silence` covers cases where the expression remains invalid even after stabilising — showing nothing is better than a permanent error message.

---

!! Input notation

Input must use EN/international notation:

|!Format |!Example |
|Decimal point |`3.14` |
|Thousands space (U+0020, U+00A0, U+2009, U+202F) |`1 000 000` |
|Scientific notation |`5e9` · `1.5e-3` · `2.5e+6` |
|Scientific with stray space |`5 e9` (auto-normalised to `5e9`) |

⚠️ Do ''not'' write `5 * e9` — that means 5 times the undefined symbol `e9`.

