---

!! Usage

!!! Basic

<$codeblock code="<$calc>1 + 2 * 3</$calc>"/>

!!! Locale

Controls output decimal separator, thousands separator, and digit grouping.

<$codeblock code="""<$calc locale="fr-FR">1234567.89</$calc>"""/>

Short aliases: `en` → `en-US`, `fr` → `fr-FR`. Any valid BCP-47 tag works.

!!! Show modes

<$codeblock code="""<$calc show="result">sqrt(2)</$calc>
<$calc show="formula">sqrt(2)</$calc>
<$calc show="full" mode="block">sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$calc>"""/>

!!! Block display

<$codeblock code="""<$calc mode="block">pi * r^2</$calc>"""/>

!!! Silence errors

<$codeblock code="""<$calc silence="yes">bad expression</$calc>"""/>

!!! Notation

<$codeblock code="""<$calc notation="scientific">0.00000012</$calc>
<$calc notation="engineering" locale="fr">1234567</$calc>
<$calc notation="fixed" precision="2">3.14159</$calc>
<$calc notation="bin">42</$calc>
<$calc notation="oct">42</$calc>
<$calc notation="hex">255</$calc>"""/>

!!! Variable scope — tiddler mode

<$codeblock code="""<$calc scope="MyVars">pi * r^2</$calc>"""/>

`MyVars` is a tiddler with one `name: expression` per line, evaluated in order:

```
r: 5
h: 10
vol: pi * r^2 * h
```

!!! Variable scope — inline mode

<$codeblock code="""<$calc scope="{r: 3, h: 10}">pi * r^2 * h</$calc>"""/>

Key rules: valid mathjs identifiers (`[a-zA-Z_$][a-zA-Z0-9_$]*`), values in EN notation, pairs separated by commas, `math.unit(5 cm)` auto-quoted.

!!! BigNumber precision

<$codeblock code="""<$calc calcPrec="64">1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13</$calc>"""/>

With `calcPrec="64/128/256"`, all numeric literals are automatically BigNumber — no need for `math.bignumber()`.

!!! Units

<$codeblock code="""<$calc>9.81 m/s^2 * 80 kg</$calc>
<$calc>460 V * 20 A * 30 days to kWh</$calc>
<$calc>100 degF to degC</$calc>"""/>

---

!! Reserved identifiers

mathjs pre-defines two single-letter constants:

|!Identifier |!mathjs meaning |
| `e` |Euler's number — 2.718281828… (also `ℯ` U+212F) |
| `i` |imaginary unit — √−1 |

Defining `e` or `i` in the `scope` silently shadows these constants. Use `euler`, `base`, `idx`, `imag`, etc. instead.

---

!! Precision and performance

!!! Default mode: float

By default the widget uses native IEEE 754 `float64` (~16 significant digits). The formatter caps output at `precision` decimal places, which suppresses most float artefacts:

|!Expression |!Raw float value |!Displayed |
| `0.1 + 0.2` |`0.30000000000000004` |`0.3` ✅ |
| `9.81 * 80` |`784.8000000000001` |`784.8` ✅ |

!!! When to use BigNumber

Switch only when float produces a ''visibly wrong result'':

|!Situation |!Example |!float |!BigNumber |
|Catastrophic cancellation |`1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13` |`1.234375` ❌ |`1.23456789` ✅ |
|Subtraction residual |`0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1` |`-2.78e-17` ❌ |`0` ✅ |
|Integer > MAX_SAFE_INTEGER |`9007199254740993` |`9007199254740992` ❌ |`9007199254740993` ✅ |

!!! Precision modes

|!`calcPrec` |!Engine |!Significant digits |!Typical cost vs float |
| `float` (default) |IEEE 754 float64 |~16 |1× baseline |
| `64` |BigNumber |64 |~3–4× slower |
| `128` |BigNumber |128 |~5–6× slower |
| `256` |BigNumber |256 |~8–10× slower |

!!! Display vs internal precision

`calcPrec` controls internal accuracy. `precision` controls visible digits. Raising `calcPrec` does ''not'' add visible digits — it only reduces rounding errors in intermediate calculations.

Note on BigNumber digit counts: `calcPrec="64"` means 64 ''decimal'' significant digits (~213 bits), not 64 bits. Do not confuse with IEEE 754 bit widths (`calcPrec="128"` is ~425 bits).

!!! Performance thresholds

|!`calcPrec` |!µs/eval (arithmetic) |!µs/eval (`sin`/`cos`) |!Widgets before 16 ms jank |
| `float` |~13 µs |~14 µs |>1 000 ✅ |
| `64` |~66 µs |~925 µs |~240 arith. / ~17 trig |
| `128` |~169 µs |~1 957 µs |~94 arith. / ~8 trig |
| `256` |~89 µs |~5 346 µs |~180 arith. / ~3 trig |

The LRU cache (500 entries) means each unique expression is evaluated only once per tiddler change.

!!! Hard limit: trig functions at high precision

`sin`, `cos`, `tan`, `asin`, `acos`, `atan`, `sinh`, `cosh` throw `[DecimalError] Precision limit exceeded` at precision ≥ 510. The widget caps BigNumber options at `256`, safely within this limit.

---

!! Limitations

* Not a spreadsheet — no dependency graph between tiddlers
* No reactive variable propagation across widgets
* Sandbox is heuristic, not a secure VM
* KaTeX output covers common cases; advanced LaTeX (`\color`, `\align`, `\underbrace`) requires raw LaTeX via `<$katex />`

